<FIRST>d a PM-BRF--LittleLeagueCrash     06-05 0167</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Little League Crash,0170</SECOND>
<HEAD>Little League Coach, Players Die in Crash</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CLOVERDALE, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A truck slammed head-on into a station
wagon taking a Little League baseball coach and team members to a
game, killing the man and five of his players, the highway patrol
said.
   Killed in Sunday's accident on rain-slick Highway 101 north of
Cloverdale were Roy Daniel Jr., 44, a Mark West Little League
coach; his sons Roy Daniel III, 16, and Shane Daniel, 10; Nick
Mataya, 16; Brent Towers, 17; and Nate Bartholomew, 16.
   Daniel's wife, Darlyene, 42, was in critical condition at
Healdsburg General Hospital. The driver of the truck was treated
and released.
   The truck was going about 50 mph when it skidded on the wet road
and crossed into the opposite lane, crashing into Daniel's car,
said John Mede, a state Highway Patrol information officer.
   Daniel was one of several people driving team members to Fort
Bragg for a game, said Mark West Youth Club President Richard
Mikulich.
</TEXT>
