<SECOND>AM-Haiti-Fire,0204</SECOND>
<HEAD>Fire Destroys One of Two Hospitals, Four Dead</HEAD>
<TEXT>
   PORT-AU-PRINCE, Haiti (AP) _ A fire engulfed one of the
capital's two public hospitals, destroying most of its facilities
and killing four people, including a baby in an incubator, a radio
station reported Monday.
   The independent radio station Haiti-Inter said the fire broke
out at 3 a.m. Sunday at Hospital de L'Asile in downtown
Port-au-Prince and destroyed two operating rooms, the maternity
ward, the pharmacy, laboratory and administrative offices.
   ``My wife was in labor. She had to jump out of a window of the
maternity ward to save herself and our unborn baby,'' one man said
on condition of anonymity.
   In addition to the baby, an adult patient and two visitors were
killed. Two others, including a nurse, were injured.
   The public hospital, one of two in the city of 1 million people,
was founded in 1878. It employs 180 people and has 59 beds,
compared with 1,000 beds in the State University Hospital.
   Haiti-Inter said that before the fire, two power failures
blacked out the area and shooting was reported in the neighborhood.
   Hospital administrators said they were awaiting results of a
police investigation before commenting.
</TEXT>
