<SECOND>AM-Colombia-Ferry,0137</SECOND>
<HEAD>River Ferry Capsizes 8 Drown, 21 Missing</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BOGOTA, Colombia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A river ferry crowded with people
returning from a gold-mining community's beauty queen contest
capsized Monday, drowning eight people and leaving 21 missing,
according to the National Radio Network.
   It said 25 survivors were injured in the early morning accident
on the Condoto River near the town of Andagoya, 230 miles west of
Bogota.
   The station said the wooden ferry was carrying about 200 people
but its legal capacity is 150.
   Most of the passengers were gold miners and peasants returning
to their homes from a beauty contest and festival in Andagoya, near
the Pacific coast, the broadcast reported.
   It quoted Red Cross officials as saying three adults and five
children drowned and many of the missing are children.
