<HEAD>Report Five Policemen, Seven Guerrillas Killed</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LIMA, PERU (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Rebels killed five policemen in an ambush, and
seven guerrillas were slain by soldiers in a gunfight, police and
army spokesmen reported Monday.
   Police said the five officers were killed Sunday by rebels of
the Maoist Shining Path movement in an ambush on a road near Tingo
Maria, 240 miles northeast of Lima.
   An army report said a military patrol encountered a group of
guerrillas and killed seven in a clash Thursday at Huanuco, 185
miles northeast of Lima.
   More than 14,000 people have been killed in guerrilla-related
violence since the Shining Path began its anti-government campaign
in 1980.
