<HEAD>Gulf &amp; Western Changes Name to Paramount Communications</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Gulf &amp; Western Inc. became Paramount
Communications Inc. on Monday in a name change that the company
said reflects its concentration on the entertainment and publishing
businesses.
   The company, which counts Paramount Pictures among its
operations, announced earlier this year that it intends to sell its
financial services business and devote its full attention to
entertainment and publishing.
   In connection with the name change, the company began three
weeks ago to haul down the huge 17-foot high ``G'' and ``W''
letters that marked the top of its headquarters building near
Central Park in Manhattan. The letters will not be replaced,
spokesman Jerry Sherman said.
   The company's new stock symbol is PCI and its new stock table
listing is ParaComm. The stock is traded on the New York Stock
Exchange.
