should proceed with negotiations on plans to reorganize as a
smaller carrier, possibly squelching a union-led purchase offer for
the strikebound carrier.
   Monday's decision by U.S. Bankruptcy Judge Burton R. Lifland
came after Eastern's creditors expressed reservations about the
buyout proposal from an investor group led by Eastern's unions and
Chicago commodities trader Joseph Ritchie.
   The Ritchie group had met with representatives of Eastern parent
Texas Air Corp. on Saturday but failed to win support for its
