<DATELINE>MINNEAPOLIS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   NWA Inc.'s board of directors rejected a set
of buyout offers and invited suitors to revise their bids, but the
parent of Northwest Airlines said it might not find any revision
acceptable.
   ``None of the proposals is acceptable in its present form,'' the
board's review committee said Monday in a letter to bidders.
