conditions is up and expectations remain positive about the next
six months, according to a new survey.
   More than 20 percent of 5,000 households nationwide surveyed in
May by the Conference Board said they anticipate that business
conditions will improve in the next six months, according to the
survey released Monday.
   That level was up from 17 percent a month earlier.
