turned to dollars in the face of the turmoil in Beijing. Gold
prices turned in a varied performance.
   Government bond prices finished slightly higher.
   The unrest in China stirred commodities markets, touching off an
oil futures rally, depressing sugar prices and sending cotton
futures tumbling to the daily trading limit.
